### 3.2 LangChain (Orchestration Framework)

> [!info] What it is
> LangChain is a Python framework for building LLM applications. Provides components (chains, prompts, retrievers, agents) and integrations (vector stores, LLMs).

**Why LangChain for this project:**
- Abstracts away boilerplate (embedding, retrieval, prompt building)
- Integrates with FAISS, Ollama, sentence-transformers out of the box
- Modular — swap components easily (change embeddings model, vector store, LLM)
- Production patterns (chains, memory, agents)

**LangChain Concepts You'll Use:**

**Document Loaders** — read PDFs, text files, web pages
```python
from langchain.document_loaders import PyPDFLoader
loader = PyPDFLoader("pci-dss.pdf")
docs = loader.load()
```

**Text Splitters** — chunk documents
```python
from langchain.text_splitter import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter
splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(chunk_size=1000, chunk_overlap=200)
chunks = splitter.split_documents(docs)
```

**Embeddings** — vectorize text
```python
from langchain_community.embeddings import HuggingFaceEmbeddings
embeddings = HuggingFaceEmbeddings(model_name="sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2")
```

**Vector Stores** — index and search
```python
from langchain_community.vectorstores import FAISS
vectorstore = FAISS.from_documents(chunks, embeddings)
```

**Retrievers** — fetch relevant chunks
```python
retriever = vectorstore.as_retriever(search_kwargs={"k": 4})
```

**Chains (LCEL)** — pipe components together
```python
chain = retriever | prompt | llm | output_parser
```

**Interview prep:**
- *"Why LangChain?"* → Provides building blocks for RAG — loaders, splitters, embeddings, vector stores, LLM wrappers — that work together without custom glue code
- *"LangChain vs LlamaIndex?"* → LangChain is general-purpose LLM orchestration. LlamaIndex is RAG-focused with more advanced retrieval. Both are popular
- *"What is LCEL?"* → LangChain Expression Language. Pipe-syntax for composing chains: `prompt | llm | parser`

