### 3.3 FAISS (Vector Store)

> [!info] What FAISS is
> Facebook AI Similarity Search. A library for efficient similarity search and clustering of dense vectors. Created by Meta, open-source, fast, runs in-memory.

**Why FAISS for this project:**
- Free and open-source (no API costs)
- Runs locally (privacy, no network calls)
- Very fast for similarity search
- Easy to use with Python and LangChain
- Sufficient for small/medium document corpora

**How FAISS works:**
- Stores high-dimensional vectors (e.g., 384-dimensional)
- Builds an index for efficient nearest-neighbor search
- Approximate Nearest Neighbor (ANN) algorithms for speed
- Returns top-k most similar vectors to a query vector

**FAISS Index Types:**
- **IndexFlat** — exact search, slow for large datasets
- **IndexIVF** — Inverted File Index, much faster
- **IndexHNSW** — Hierarchical Navigable Small Worlds, very fast, more memory

For your scale (few PDFs), `IndexFlat` is fine — exact and simple.

**Similarity Metrics:**
- **Cosine similarity** — angle between vectors (most common for text)
- **Dot product** — for normalized vectors, equivalent to cosine
- **L2 distance** — Euclidean distance

**Interview prep:**
- *"Why FAISS?"* → Free, local, fast for small/medium scale, integrates with LangChain
- *"FAISS vs Pinecone vs Chroma?"* → FAISS is local + library (you manage persistence). Pinecone is managed cloud. Chroma is local with persistence built-in. Choice depends on scale and ops needs
- *"How does FAISS find similar vectors?"* → For your IndexFlat case, it computes similarity between query and every vector, returns top-k. For HNSW, it traverses a small-world graph for fast approximate search
- *"What's the dimensionality of your vectors?"* → 384 (using all-MiniLM-L6-v2)

