### 3.4 sentence-transformers (Embedding Model)

> [!info] What it is
> A Python library for state-of-the-art sentence and text embeddings. Built on top of Hugging Face Transformers. Provides pretrained models that produce dense vector representations of text.

**Model you'll use: `all-MiniLM-L6-v2`**

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| **Dimensions** | 384 |
| **Speed** | Very fast (millions of sentences per second on GPU, ~14K on CPU) |
| **Size** | ~80 MB |
| **Performance** | Strong on semantic similarity benchmarks |
| **Best for** | General-purpose semantic search |

**Why this model:**
- **Free** — runs locally, no API costs
- **Fast** — small enough to embed thousands of chunks quickly on CPU
- **Good quality** — competitive with larger models for retrieval
