## 📈 PART 7 — Scaling and Production Considerations

### Indexing at Scale
- Parallelize embedding (multiprocessing)
- Batch upserts to vector DB
- Incremental indexing (only re-index changed docs)

### Retrieval Quality
- Hybrid search (BM25 + vector)
- Cross-encoder reranking
- Query expansion (rewrite query for better recall)

### LLM Layer
- Move to GPU-served larger model (Llama 3.1 70B)
- Or hybrid: small local model for simple queries, larger remote for complex
- Add streaming responses (better UX)
- Implement prompt caching

### Observability
- Log every request: question, retrieved chunks, answer, latency
- Track metrics: avg latency, retrieval quality, user satisfaction
- Sample outputs for manual quality review

### Production Deployment
- Containerize with Docker
- Deploy on GPU instance for LLM
- Vector DB as managed service (Pinecone/Qdrant Cloud)
- Load balancer in front
- Rate limiting per user

